The '''1995 All-America college football team''' is composed of the following All-American Teams: [[Associated Press]], [[United Press International]], [[Football Writers Association of America]], [[American Football Coaches Association]], [[Walter Camp Foundation]], ''[[The Sporting News]]'' and ''Football News''.<ref>[http://www.afca.com/pdf3/68830.pdf?ATCLID=289547&SPSID=69273&SPID=7863&DB_OEM_ID=9300 American Football Coaches Association] {{dead link|date=April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bQkpAAAAIBAJ&dq=1995+College+Football+All-America+Team+ap&pg=PA8&article_id=7207,6434356 |title=Associated Press |access-date=2024-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sportswriters.net/fwaa/awards/allamerica/alltime.pdf |title=Football Writers Association of America |access-date=2009-03-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151227072543/http://www.sportswriters.net/fwaa/awards/allamerica/alltime.pdf |archive-date=2015-12-27 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>[http://www.sportingnews.com/archives/almanac/nfl/cfbamer.html The Sporting News] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090227143400/http://www.sportingnews.com/archives/almanac/nfl/cfbamer.html |date=2009-02-27 }}</ref><ref>[http://waltercamp.org/index.php/teams_and_awards/ Walter Camp Foundation] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090330065940/http://waltercamp.org/index.php/teams_and_awards |date=2009-03-30 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Football News All-America team|date=November 25, 1995|newspaper=Great Falls Tribune|page=2C|agency=AP|url=https://www.newspapers.com/article/great-falls-tribune/127588976/|access-date=July 4, 2023|via=[[Newspapers.com]]}}</ref>

The College Football All-America Team is an honor given annually to the best American college football players at their respective positions. The original usage of the term All-America seems to have been to such a list selected by football pioneer Walter Camp in the 1890s. The NCAA has officially recognized All-Americans selected by over a changing roster of over 20 organizations. In 1995, the official selectors were the AP, UPI, AFCA, FWAA, WCFF, TSN, and FN to determine Consensus All-Americans.

The Newspaper Enterprise Association (NEA), the oldest All-American college football selection at the time and once an official selector, also selected a team.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Siner |first1=Howard |title=Tommie Frazer leads All-Americans |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1NcgAAAAIBAJ&pg=PA7&dq=NEA+All-American+team+Football&article_id=1369,5031580&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiP8fW3qvCSAxXsEVkFHbaSOeYQ6AF6BAgMEAM#v=onepage&q=NEA%20All-American%20team%20Football&f=false |access-date=25 February 2026 |work=McCook Daily Gazette |date=13 December 1995}}</ref>

